Parliament, Thursday, 22 November 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Arts and Culture will tomorrow conclude its week-long interviews for the Pan South African Language Board (PanSALB). The committee interviews 25 shortlisted candidates this week. The public is invited to attend the interview sessions and submit comments to the committee secretary, Ms Ajabulile Mtiya, via email: amtiya@parliament.gov.za or fax: 086 544 0628 by Wednesday, 28 November 2018. Interviews for Friday, 23 November 2018 will be conducted as follows: Date : Friday, 23 November 2018
	Time : 09:30 – 16:00
	
	Venue: Committee Room G26, Ground Floor, National Assembly Building, ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ARTS AND CULTURE, MS XOLISWA TOM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
